subject: Enable a bunch of clang-tidy checks
commitMessage:
Enable a bunch of clang-tidy checks

New year, new set of clang-tidy checks we can enable.  This clang-tidy
list was brought over from bmcweb.  Most of the fixes are relatively
trivial.

This probably should be broke down more.  As-is, it's kind of a big
change.

Tested: TBD

Signed-off-by: Ed Tanous <edtanous@google.com>
Change-Id: I10d4f617604dcd849ea3423fe65b30095652e2c4

Surely you could automate this into adding one new check per patch with the associated fixes?

Considering that most the changes are manually done, it's not automatable easily, but I'm happy to split it up.  I did the same thing for bmcweb.  "git add -p" works pretty well for splitting up stuff like this.

ACK
Broke this patchset out quite a bit.  It's now +90 -87 lines, down from 300, and 34 of those lines are actually adding the clang tidy checks.  Will continue to do more breakdowns tomorrow.
Okay, I figured the fixes were automated :grimace:. Anyway, your `git add -p` approach is a good idea. Thanks for honouring my request :)

Yeah, it's not fun, but what's less fun than doing manual fixes to an old codebase is repeating the same "initialize your variables" comment in every code review 😊

Every clang-tidy test that I've turned on in any of the applications has been well worth the cost in review-time.
